                <h2 data-uuid="2c8bee30f2d3430eaf25f6668ad4d358"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="7a727b12edc84d8e9511489819a400a4">Part 2: Write an Analytical Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="b47a4fcdf57a44529a5efe3517571797">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="ec876fa2affa43338d059336ba0fc5ad">The postwar years brought prosperity to millions
                of Americans. Communications technologies, such as television, radio, and
                newspapers, enabled the development of mass popular culture, and more Americans
                than ever enjoyed easy travel by car on interstate highways. During the same
                period, however, the fear of communism led to tense political standoffs at home
                and global Cold War conflicts with the Soviet Union.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="3e6600eb4c14421c976b05237da50b30">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="504fd01380874a4599b6fe36b57da136">As American incomes grew, more people gained
                access to mass communications, such as television. Journalists and politicians
                used these communications both to inform the public and to give their opinion
                of events. Did use of mass communications unnecessarily worsen citizensâ€™ fear
                of communism? Write an analytical essay in which you respond to this question.</p>
            <p data-uuid="04d48440e9d94f2cb17fdd73fe7230dc">Complete
                the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="1fbc560573ea47f681854c90d0d8c2a3">
                <li data-uuid="e2f63d0ef97f4ddca3806e7238fa8e30">
                    <p data-uuid="9f367d994588428ca53ef9c4a35ef58b">Review
                        your notes and sources before you start writing.</p>
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="9a85d9a788e5473ca63dc3b579e9bcf8">
                    <p data-uuid="b73689fa38fe40fc9510d46c9b5f8b8a">Use
                        at least two of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant,
                        well-chosen text or visual evidence from the documents.<br />
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="8fa7813c3a394a39aebaba9eee76823b">
                    Cite
                    specific text or visual evidence from each of the sources in your response.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="6c3b2ddf4eff4eb6952dc6c7aa9e38ae">
                    Plan
                    your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a
                    concluding paragraph.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="6dfb1a2660754f528f6e94b6e5db598a">
                    Organize
                    your essay in a clear and logical way that expresses a firm standpoint about
                    the topic.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="aae356965a64448c88984993e69448d7">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information
                    you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
